# llm-calibration-eval

[![CI](https://github.com/vvvaibhaverma-123459876/llm-calibration-eval/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/vvvaibhaverma-123459876/llm-calibration-eval/actions/workflows/ci.yml)
[![Python 3.11+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.11+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](LICENSE)

**Measure and improve LLM confidence calibration.**

A well-calibrated model says "I'm 90% confident" when it's correct 90% of the time.  
`llm-calibration-eval` feeds questions with known answers to LLMs, collects their stated confidence, and computes standard calibration metrics — Brier score, ECE, and reliability diagrams.

---

## Features

- Built-in 50-item trivia dataset with known ground-truth answers
- Three provider adapters: OpenAI (`gpt-4o-mini`), Anthropic (`claude-haiku-4-5`), and a deterministic Mock
- Calibration metrics: **Brier score**, **Expected Calibration Error (ECE)**, reliability diagram data
- Temperature scaling post-hoc calibration
- Matplotlib reliability diagram plots
- CLI entrypoint: `python -m llm_calibration_eval run --provider <name> --dataset trivia`
- Fully typed, >80% test coverage, GitHub Actions CI

---

## Installation

```bash
# Basic install (mock provider works without any API keys)
pip install -e .

# With OpenAI support
pip install -e ".[openai]"

# With Anthropic support
pip install -e ".[anthropic]"

# Everything including dev tools
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

---

## Quick Start

### Run with the mock provider (no API key needed)

```bash
python -m llm_calibration_eval run --provider mock --dataset trivia
```

### Run with OpenAI

```bash
export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
python -m llm_calibration_eval run --provider openai --dataset trivia
```

### Run with Anthropic

```bash
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
python -m llm_calibration_eval run --provider anthropic --dataset trivia
```

### Show a reliability diagram

```bash
python -m llm_calibration_eval run --provider mock --dataset trivia --plot
```

### Limit to N samples (for quick testing)

```bash
python -m llm_calibration_eval run --provider openai --dataset trivia --n 10
```

